postcontent:
Willing to ship product
The reliability of a steel magazine, the durability of a polymer magazine and the weight of an aluminum magazine. The L5AWM fills the gap between the current metal and polymer magazine designs combing the best features from both designs into a unique hybrid magazine. Unique to the L5AWM is the one piece wrap‐around hardened steel feed lip assembly that is permanently attached to an impact resistant polymer body. The hardened steel feed lips won’t bend, break or deform due to rough handling or long term storage. An aggressive surface texture has been applied to the polymer body to improve gripping and retrieval from pouches. The combination of steel and polymer result in a lightweight, robust magazine tough enough for professional use. The internal geometry of the Advanced Warfighter Magazine is a constant curve that has been maximized to feed the 5.56X45mm NATO round and has a non‐tilting follower for trouble‐free feeding. The feed lips are made from a single piece of precision formed steel that is hardened, then PTFE coated for corrosion resistance. The body and component materials are corrosion and chemical resistant, passing military chemical testing, including exposure to DEET. The L5 AWM is compatible with modern weapon systems; M4/M16/AR, HK416, SCAR16, and the ARX160, to name a few, and available in 10, 20 and 30 round capacity with a translucent or opaque polymer body. title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch MR762A1 7.62x51mm 16.5"
postcontent:
This is a brand new in box Heckler & Koch MR762A1 semi-automatic rifle chambered for 7.62x51mm NATO. Like the MR556A1, the MR762A1 is a direct descendent of the HK416/417 series, developed by H&K as a premium commercial/civilian market rifle with match capability. Like the HK416, the MR762A1 offers many improvements over conventional AR-10/LR-308 pattern rifles and carbines.

The MR762A1 uses H&K's proprietary gas piston operation system, employing a piston and a solid rod in place of the gas tube found on typical AR-10/LR-308 pattern firearms. This method of operation virtually eliminates malfunctions common to direct impingement gas systems since the hot carbon fouling and waste gasses do not enter the receiver. This keeps the receiver much cleaner and decreases heat wear to internal componentry. The service life of all parts is increased substantially. This is the same key feature critical to the success of the HK416 rifles used by leading military and law enforcement customers.

The MR762A1 is produced in the USA using American and German made components, and uses many of the same assemblies and accessories originally developed for the HK416/417 series, including the HK free-floating four-quadrant rail system. The HK Free Floating Rail System handguard has four MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rails and allows all current accessories, sights, lights, and aimers used on M4/M16-type arms to be fitted to the MR Series. The HK rail system can be installed and removed with simple tools and returns to zero when reinstalled.

The upper receiver has a Picatinny rail machined in to it's top for mounting optics and BUIS. Like the HK416, the MR762A1 uses a Cold Hammer Forged barrel, in this case measuring at 16.5". The highest quality steel is used, and Cold Hammer Forging produces some of the longest lasting, most accurate barrels available. This barrel features a popular 1:12" twist rate, perfect for most commercial ammunition.

A precision enhanced two-stage trigger is equipped for significantly improved accuracy, and an extended latch charging handle makes operating the rifle with a scope easier. The stock is adjustable, and can be locked in place with an allen screw for complete security.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Civil War era S&W model one, 2nd issue .22 pocket revolver
postcontent:
S&W model one, 2nd issue .22 pocket revolver S# 65548 for sale or trade. The model one, was the first firearm the newly formed Smith and Wesson company produced. It was one of the world's very first cartridge revolvers and it was also the world's first gun to be chambered in .22 rimfire. The design was popular enough that the patent had to be defended (successfully) in court.  What a great time to start a firearms company with the Civil War starting a few years later. The model one may have been an effective close  quarters self defense gun in a world of mostly single shots with laborious reloads. 

This particular revolver was made early enough that is was likely carried during the Civil War, but it is still in working order! It was recently fired using ORIGIONAL BLACK POWER ONLY .22 SHORT cartridges. Though most of the original silver plating is intact, some of the brass frame can be seen on the wear points. Some of the original bluing is still on the barrel and cylinder and the bore is clean with sharp rifling. As a point of interest, the rifling has no twists but is straight. The butt has a few dents... isn't in funny how some people will use a fine firearm as a hammer? Also one of the grips may have been chipped during the aforementioned hammering and was repaired. The revolver appears to have been disassembled and a few of the pins were replaced. All in all this is a very nice relic of the Civil War era and of early S&W revolver development. Feel free to ask questions or make corrections to my commentary. Asking $350. including shipping. First "I'll take it" or trade, I like Glocks and military pattern firearms and silver. You can also text me at REDACTED.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Indiana Deer Legal Remington Model 700  350 JR
postcontent:
Two years ago it was illegal to hunt in Indiana with a rifle like this.
 Last year Indiana changed the casing length to 1.8 inches.  I have a gunsmith
 CF Gunworks LLC  that took  the 350 Remington Magnum  and shortened that casing to 1.8 inches
 Which is what this cartridge now is. You can’t  buy this ammo or the gun ,they 
 have to be custom made which is why they are expensive. The .357 and .44 magnums are just another example of Indiana Deer Legal cartridges that you can use. This is a High Powered Rifle that has been modified to meet Indiana specs and requirements . This rifle is 100 % legal to hunt with in Indiana .
Don’t wait for Deer season to decide you want one, you won’t be able to. This is someone’s chance to own
a very nice Indiana Deer Legal High Powered Rifle of which only a hand full are available.

I have a custom built Remington Model 700 That was a 350 Remington Magnum
it has been shortened to 1.8 inch. Indiana Deer Legal casing
the factory barrel has been bedded and set back to shorten the chamber.
It comes with Redding Dies that have been ground to match. 
I have brass and about 30rds of ammo that was made by C F Gunworks.
It is toped off with a leupold 3x9.
This rifle killed 3 deer at over 300yds this past season. It is amazing!!
I would like $1600 with scope or $1400 without.

This Rifle was custom built to Indiana Specs!!!!! And is referred to as a 350 JR
 This cartridge is modeled after the Remington 350 Magnum. They shorten the case
 to 1.8 inches, I took a picture so you can see the cartridge, bullet is 200grn
and clearly meets Indiana guide lines. I hope this helps with the confusion. 
Certain rifles like the .357 magnum or .44 magnum can be bought at walmart
and are perfectly legal. Indiana says you can't go below .357 magnum. This rifle can't
be bought at WalMart they have to be custom made which the price reflects

title: For Sale:  WW2 Red Army SVT-40, 7.62 x 54
postcontent: I have for sale a WW2, Russian SVT-40. It was manufactured at Tula in 1941 and it has all the proper parts for a rifle of this date. The SVT-40's made late in the war are very rough but this is an early war manufacture and is still in beautiful shape. All of the serial numbers match, with the exception of the magazine. It has a good bore, shoots excellent, and it,s stock is original to this rifle, with matching serial number. This is not a  replacement AVT-40 stock like so  many of these guns have, this has an SVT-40 stock with only one notch for the safety lever. It is one of the guns that were refinished by the Russians after the war. It comes with a russian leather sling, oiler, and gas adjustment tool.
